<s> Hi Blake, On a related note, it seems like encoding transforms (such as Base64 or compression or anything that significantly permutes the input data) would violate the "See what you sign" rule.  </s>
<s> A transforms such as base64, compression, etc. do not violate "What you 'see' is what you sign?", provided that the transformation algorithms follow well-documented public standards.  </s>
<s> For example, when you sign the binary of a jpeg image, are you signing what you see?  </s>
<s> No you're signing highly compressed (possibly lossy) data that corresponds to a bitmap image via a well-known public algorithm, so we accept it.  </s>
<s> By comparison, signing a base-64 encoding of a jpeg is peanuts.  </s>
