<s> Note, it's a more verbose restatment (with examples) of what is already said in the spec: Some applications might operate over the original or intermediary data but should be extremely careful about potential weaknesses introduced between the original and transformed data.  </s>
<s> This is a trust decision about the character and meaning of the transforms that an application needs to make with caution.  </s>
<s> Consider a canonicalization algorithm that normalizes character case (lower to upper) or character composition ('e and accent' to 'accented-e').  </s>
<s> An adversary could introduce changes that are normalized and consequently inconsequential to signature validity but material to a DOM processor.  </s>
<s> For instance, by changing the case of a character one might influence the result of an XPath selection.  </s>
<s> A serious risk is introduced if that change is normalized for signature validation but the processor operates over the original data and returns a different result than intended.  </s>
<s> That's a mistake.  </s>
